{
  "text": "are the values of r at which the outer (+) and inner (\u2212) horizons are placed, if they are real, as we are going to assume here. On the other hand, the dimensional reduction of the Kalb-Ramond 2-form only gives a dyonic vector field B \u00b5 with equal (up to signs) electric and magnetic charges (proportional to the constant p in the solution), whose field strength F(B) \u00b5\u03bd squares to zero. [CITATION_1] It is this property that allows us to have a constant Kaluza-Klein scalar in the z direction, since the equation of motion of that scalar would be \u2207 2 k \u223c F 2 . The dilaton field is also constant in d = 4.",
